      • checksum

        public final Type_uint checksum
        adler32 checksum of the rest of the file (everything but magic and this field); used to detect file corruption.

      • signature

        public final Type_ubyte[] signature
        SHA-1 signature (hash) of the rest of the file (everything but DexFile.DEX_FILE_MAGIC1, DexFile.DEX_FILE_MAGIC2, checksum, and this field signature); used to uniquely identify files.

      • file_size

        public final Type_uint file_size
        size of the entire file (including the header_item), in bytes.

      • header_size

        public final Type_uint header_size
        size of the header (this entire section), in bytes. This allows for at least a limited amount of backwards/forwards compatibility without invalidating the format.

      • endian_tag

        public final Type_uint endian_tag
        Endianness tag. The value is either header_item.Endian.ENDIAN_CONSTANT or header_item.Endian.REVERSE_ENDIAN_CONSTANT.

      • link_size

        public final Type_uint link_size
        Size of the link section, or 0 if this file isn't statically linked.

      • link_off

        public final Type_uint link_off
        Offset from the start of the file to the link section, or 0 if link_size == 0. The offset, if non-zero, should be to an offset into the DexFile.link_data section. The format of the data pointed at is left unspecified by this document; this header field (and the previous) are left as hooks for use by runtime implementations.
